result.execSummary:
The defendant Max T. Winters was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer (Forfeiture). This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 3:29 PM.
Defendant Max T. Winters not in court.  Attorney Katherine Cook appeared via video for Max T. Winters.  Attorney Trenton Piltz appeared in court for State of Wisconsin.
Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. 
State moves to amend Count 1 to County Ordinance-Obstructing an Officer. 
Court accepts the amendment. The Defendant is defaulted/sentenced to Court Costs.
Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
Status conference on May 13, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
Status conference on May 13, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

1:33 PM case called. Prosecuting attorney Trenton John Piltz Mr in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Max T. Winters not in court.  Attorney Katherine Cook in court for Max T. Winters. 
Defense has no information as to the defendant's non appearance. State moves to amend count 1 to a county ordinance for obstructing an officer and asks the court to default the defendant based on the non appearance. Court accepts motion, finds the defendant Guilty and orders court costs only. 
1:36 PM back on the record. Prosecuting attorney Trenton John Piltz Mr in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Max T. Winters in court.  Attorney Katherine Cook in court for Max T. Winters. 
Defense asks Court to re open the case so she can speak with her client. Court clarifies the matter is still a criminal offense and is not to be amended to a county ordinance. A Status conference is scheduled for 5/13/22 at 3:30 PM (via Zoom).
Status conference on April 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

(Case called at 3:35 PM) Defendant Max T. Winters not in court, Attorney Katherine Cook for Max T. Winters appeared in court, Attorney Robert W. Stoiber for State of Wisconsin appeared in court. 
Defense indicates the Defendant has contacted Attorney Cook stating he was held up at work. Defense requests to schedule the case for jury trial. No objection by State. 
Counsel to schedule Final Status Conference and Jury Trial with Branch 2 Judicial Assistant.
Status conference on March 17, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

(Case called at 9:46 AM- by Zoom) Prosecuting attorney Robert W. Stoiber appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin,  Attorney Katherine Cook appeared in court for Max T. Winters. Defendant Max T. Winters appeared by phone. 
Defendant enters Not Guilty pleas. Court receives Not Guilty Pleas. Branch 2 for further scheduling.
